Package sep.seeter.net.message

A base interface and concrete classes for messages understood and communicated by instances of Server.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Message
    A base interface for messages that can be communicated using ClientChannel with an instance of Server.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bye
    A BYE message: Tell a Server instance to terminate this communication session.
    Publish
    A PUB message: tells a Server instance to append a list of seets from a user to each (possibly new) topic in the set of topics.
    SeetsReply
    A SEET-REPLY message: the server reply to a SEET request: the list of lines recorded by the server for the specified topic, listed from the specified index.
    SeetsReq
    A SEET message: tells a Server instance to return the currently recorded (sub)list of seets for a given topic, as listed from the specified index (inclusive, starting from index 0).
    TopicsReply
    A TOPIC-REPLY message: the server reply to a TOPIC request: the set of topics explicitly recorded by the server.
    TopicsReq
    A TOPIC message: tells a Server instance to return the currently recorded set of topics.

Package sep.seeter.net.message Description

A base interface and concrete classes for messages understood and communicated by instances of Server.

You can send and receive instances of these messages using the provided ClientChannel.
